---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import CTA from '../components/CTA.astro';
---

<Base title="Get Started" description="Set up Baxter in minutes — drop the harness into any project, open it in Claude Code, Cursor, or GitHub Copilot, and paste your first raw request.">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-20">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Get started with Baxter</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
      Baxter is a plain-text harness — a folder you drop into any project. No accounts, no subscriptions, no special tooling. You need git, an AI coding tool (Claude Code, Cursor, or similar), and your project's source code.
    </p>

    <!-- What you'll have at the end -->
    <div class="mt-8 rounded-xl border border-primary-200 bg-primary-50 p-5 dark:border-primary-800/40 dark:bg-primary-900/10">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary-800 dark:text-primary-300">What you'll have at the end of this guide</p>
      <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1.5 text-sm text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-400">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span>✓</span><span>Baxter installed and reading your codebase</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span>✓</span><span>Your first artefact generated and saved to git</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span>✓</span><span>A clear understanding of the core skills (templated artefacts) and the power tools (slash commands)</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- coderepo callout — must be unmissable -->
    <div class="mt-10 rounded-xl border-2 border-primary-500 bg-primary-50 p-6 dark:border-primary-700 dark:bg-primary-950/30">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400">Most important step — where does my code go?</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">→ <code class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400">coderepo/</code></p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Copy or symlink your project's source code into the <code class="rounded bg-white px-1 dark:bg-zinc-900">coderepo/</code> folder. Baxter reads it to run multi-dimensional sanity checking on every artefact — feasibility, logic, data model, roles, naming, edge cases, and UX challenges. Without this, artefact verification cannot run.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-primary-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-primary-800">
        <pre class="p-4 text-xs text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">agentic-ba/
├── <span class="text-primary-400 font-bold">coderepo/</span>                  ← YOUR PROJECT SOURCE CODE HERE
│   └── (your app, API, schema, migrations…)
├── artefacts/
│   ├── bug-reports/           ← bug reports
│   ├── change-requests/       ← change requests
│   ├── ai-feature-requests/   ← AI feature specs
│   ├── requirements/          ← business requirements documents
│   ├── product-docs/          ← product documentation
│   ├── implementation-plans/  ← technical implementation plans
│   ├── test-suites/           ← test cases
│   ├── diagrams/              ← diagrams and ERDs
│   └── client-clarifications/ ← client clarification requests
├── templates/                 ← core skills: BR, CR, AI, BRD, PD, TIP, TC, DIA, ERD, CLQ
├── .claude/commands/          ← power tools: nine slash-command workflows
├── preferences.json           ← optional configuration
└── CLAUDE.md</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-700 bg-zinc-950">
        <div class="border-b border-zinc-800 px-4 py-2 text-xs text-zinc-500">three ways to add your code</div>
        <pre class="p-4 text-xs text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed"># Copy your project in
cp -r /path/to/your/project coderepo/

# Or symlink it (keeps one copy on disk)
ln -s /path/to/your/project coderepo/src

# Or clone a sub-repo into it
git clone https://github.com/your-org/your-project coderepo/</pre>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-500">
        Anything you drop into <code class="rounded bg-white px-1 dark:bg-zinc-900">coderepo/</code> is gitignored and never committed — your code stays private to your machine. The same applies to <code class="rounded bg-white px-1 dark:bg-zinc-900">artefacts/</code>: every BRD, CR, TC, sample data file, or other generated output stays local and is never pushed to GitHub.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 space-y-12">

      <!-- Step 1 -->
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">1</span>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Clone or copy the harness</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-zinc-700">
          <pre class="p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">git clone https://github.com/glovarix/agentic-ba.git
cd agentic-ba</pre>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          Or copy the folder into an existing project repo. The harness is self-contained — it does not affect your project's code or CI.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 2 -->
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">2</span>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Add your codebase</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          Copy or symlink your project's source code into <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">coderepo/</code>. This is what Baxter reads to verify every artefact — required for everything except an initial BRD.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-zinc-700">
          <pre class="p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">cp -r /path/to/your/project coderepo/</pre>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-4 dark:border-amber-800/40 dark:bg-amber-900/10">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300">Your code never leaves your machine</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">Everything inside <code class="rounded bg-white px-1 dark:bg-zinc-900">coderepo/</code> is gitignored — it is never committed or pushed. If your codebase is large, a symlink works just as well as a copy.</p>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          Baxter reads <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">coderepo/</code> to verify every artefact against your real codebase — checking technical feasibility, logic consistency, data model implications, role and permission logic, and flagging missing edge cases.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 3 -->
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">3</span>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Open in your AI agent</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          Open the folder in your AI agent. Baxter's instructions are already in the right file for each tool — the agent loads them automatically with no setup.
        </p>

        <!-- Recommended for beginners -->
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border-2 border-primary-400 bg-primary-50 p-4 dark:border-primary-600 dark:bg-primary-950/30">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-400">Recommended for beginners</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">VS Code + the Claude Code extension</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
            If you are new to this, install <a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary-600 underline underline-offset-2 dark:text-primary-400">VS Code</a> and add the <strong>Claude Code extension</strong> from the marketplace. You get a familiar editor with Baxter running in a side panel — no terminal required. Open the <code class="rounded bg-white px-1 dark:bg-zinc-900">agentic-ba</code> folder, open the Claude Code panel, and start pasting requests.
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          It works just as well in the Claude Code CLI, Cursor, or VS Code with GitHub Copilot — each picks up its own instruction file:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700">
          <table class="w-full text-sm">
            <thead class="border-b border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-900">
              <tr>
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Tool</th>
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Instruction file loaded automatically</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-100 dark:divide-zinc-800">
              {[
                { tool: 'VS Code + Claude Code extension  (recommended)', file: 'CLAUDE.md' },
                { tool: 'Claude Code (CLI)', file: 'CLAUDE.md' },
                { tool: 'Cursor', file: '.cursor/rules/baxter.mdc' },
                { tool: 'GitHub Copilot', file: '.github/copilot-instructions.md' },
              ].map((row) => (
                <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950">
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-200">{row.tool}</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400">{row.file}</td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          The instruction files are identical (both Claude Code editions read <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">CLAUDE.md</code>). A pre-commit hook keeps them in sync — edit <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">CLAUDE.md</code> and the others update automatically on your next commit. Run this once after cloning to activate it:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-3 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-zinc-700">
          <pre class="p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">git config core.hooksPath .githooks</pre>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 4 -->
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-primary-600 text-sm font-bold text-white">4</span>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Paste a request — any raw text</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-zinc-700">
          <div class="border-b border-zinc-800 px-4 py-2 text-xs text-zinc-500">example requests — paste exactly as received</div>
          <div class="space-y-3 p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">
            <p>"The login page returns a 500 error when the user submits without a password"</p>
            <p class="border-t border-zinc-800 pt-3">"Write up the BRD for care plan cloning"</p>
            <p class="border-t border-zinc-800 pt-3">"I need test cases for the vitals module — mandatory fields and role access"</p>
            <p class="border-t border-zinc-800 pt-3">"Add a print to PDF button to the patient profile page"</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
          Baxter classifies the request, tells you which template it will use, and asks for a one-word confirmation before generating anything. You can reply with the artefact code (e.g. <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">BR</code>), a number, or just <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">proceed</code>.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- What to say for each artefact -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">What to say for each artefact</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        You never name a template — just describe what you need in plain language. Add your codebase to <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">coderepo/</code>, paste any raw request into Claude Code, Cursor, or GitHub Copilot, and Baxter classifies it, runs the full multi-dimensional sanity check against your source files, and asks before saving. The example prompts are illustrative; the signal words show what Baxter listens for. Power tools are not listed here — they are slash commands, covered in the power tools section below.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="border-b border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-900">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Artefact</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Example prompt — paste raw text like this</th>
              <th class="hidden px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white sm:table-cell">Signal words Baxter listens for</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-100 dark:divide-zinc-800">
            {[
              { icon: '🐛', name: 'Bug Report (BR)', prompt: '"The reports endpoint returns 500 when a duplicate name is submitted"', signals: '"not working", "broken", "error", "404", "500", "crash", "fails"' },
              { icon: '🔄', name: 'Change Request (CR)', prompt: '"Add a bulk export option to the orders list"', signals: '"add", "new", "improve", "enhance", "change", "feature request"' },
              { icon: '🤖', name: 'AI Feature (AI)', prompt: '"We need an AI feature to auto-suggest categories from the item description"', signals: '"AI feature", "auto-fill", "auto-generate", "suggest", "LLM"' },
              { icon: '📋', name: 'Business Requirements (BRD) — pre-dev', prompt: '"Write up the requirements for recurring invoices"', signals: '"BRD", "business requirements", "spec for", "write up the requirements"' },
              { icon: '📖', name: 'Product Documentation (PD) — post-dev', prompt: '"Document the authentication module"', signals: '"PD", "document the module", "how it works", "what was built"' },
              { icon: '🏗️', name: 'Implementation Plan (TIP)', prompt: '"Write an implementation plan for the bulk import feature"', signals: '"TIP", "implementation plan", "how to build", "dev plan"' },
              { icon: '🧪', name: 'Test Cases (TC)', prompt: '"Generate test cases for the billing module"', signals: '"test cases", "test suite", "QA cases", "test steps"' },
              { icon: '🗂️', name: 'Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD)', prompt: '"Draw an ERD for the orders and customers tables"', signals: '"ERD", "entity relationship", "data model diagram", "draw the schema", "show the tables"' },
              { icon: '📐', name: 'Diagram (DIA)', prompt: '"Diagram the checkout flow from API request to database"', signals: '"diagram", "flowchart", "mermaid", "draw", "visualise", "sequence diagram", "state diagram"' },
            ].map((row) => (
              <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top">
                  <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
                    <span>{row.icon}</span>
                    <span class="font-medium text-zinc-800 dark:text-zinc-200">{row.name}</span>
                  </div>
                </td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top text-xs italic text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">{row.prompt}</td>
                <td class="hidden px-4 py-3 align-top text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400 sm:table-cell">{row.signals}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-3 text-xs text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Baxter applies the first match in priority order, confirms the template, and asks before saving. If nothing matches, it asks you one clarifying question. These prompts are illustrative — phrase yours however you like.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Preferences -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Configuring Baxter</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Drop a <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">preferences.json</code> file in the project root to change how Baxter behaves. All settings are optional — Baxter runs on the defaults below if the file is absent.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-950 dark:border-zinc-700">
        <div class="border-b border-zinc-800 px-4 py-2 text-xs text-zinc-500">preferences.json — all defaults shown</div>
        <pre class="p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300">{`{
  "pushAfterCommit":       false,
  "confirmBeforeSave":     true,
  "confirmBeforeCommit":   true,
  "confirmBeforeGenerate": true,
  "runSanityCheck":           true,
  "includeTechnicalNotes":    true,
  "includeAcceptanceCriteria": true,
  "language":                 "en-GB"
}`}</pre>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="border-b border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-900">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Setting</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Default</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">What it controls</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-100 dark:divide-zinc-800">
            {[
              { key: 'pushAfterCommit', default: 'false', description: 'Push to remote automatically after every commit. When false, you push manually.' },
              { key: 'confirmBeforeSave', default: 'true', description: 'Ask before writing any artefact file. Set to false to save immediately.' },
              { key: 'confirmBeforeCommit', default: 'true', description: 'Ask before running any git commit. Set to false to commit without prompting.' },
              { key: 'confirmBeforeGenerate', default: 'true', description: 'Announce the classified artefact type and ask for confirmation before generating. Set to false to skip straight to output.' },
              { key: 'runSanityCheck', default: 'true', description: 'Read coderepo/ and run the full sanity check after every applicable artefact. Set to false for faster, unverified drafts.' },
              { key: 'includeTechnicalNotes', default: 'true', description: 'Include the Technical Notes section in all artefacts. Set to false to omit it — useful for non-technical audiences.' },
              { key: 'includeAcceptanceCriteria', default: 'true', description: 'Include an Acceptance Criteria section in Change Request (CR) and Bug Report (BR) artefacts where applicable. Set to false to omit it from both. Other artefact types are unaffected.' },
              { key: 'language', default: '"en-GB"', description: 'Writing language. Use "en-GB" for UK English or "en-US" for US English.' },
            ].map((row) => (
              <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400">{row.key}</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs text-zinc-500">{row.default}</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 text-xs text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">{row.description}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Power tools -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Power tools — slash commands</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Everything above is a <strong class="text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">core skill</strong> — a templated artefact you invoke by pasting raw text. <strong class="text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Power tools</strong> are nine automation workflows you run explicitly as slash commands. Each confirms before saving and exports a PDF automatically where applicable; the full output structure lives in each command file in <code class="rounded bg-zinc-100 px-1 dark:bg-zinc-800">.claude/commands/</code>.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-700">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="border-b border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 dark:border-zinc-700 dark:bg-zinc-900">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Command</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">What it's for</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">What you provide</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-100 dark:divide-zinc-800">
            {[
              { cmd: '/generate-module-registry', use: 'Builds the module registry Baxter checks module names against in every artefact.', provide: 'Nothing — just run it. Writes artefacts/modules/modules.md.' },
              { cmd: '/generate-test-plan', use: 'Synthesises a full, structured test plan from an existing test suite, plus PDF.', provide: 'A test-suite folder of *_TC*.md files, or pick one when prompted.' },
              { cmd: '/generate-release-notes', use: 'Pre-release notes grouped by module, with GitHub and ClickUp links, plus PDF.', provide: 'A sprint number and the GitHub issue numbers to include.' },
              { cmd: '/validate-release', use: 'Confirms every release-note item is on staging, flags undocumented changes and DB migrations, plus PDF.', provide: 'Release notes path, two branch snapshots in coderepo/branches/, and a sprint number.' },
              { cmd: '/compare-branches', use: 'Diffs two branch snapshots — technical, plain-English, or both — plus PDF.', provide: 'Two branch folders in coderepo/branches/ (folder name becomes the label).' },
              { cmd: '/generate-samples', beta: true, use: 'Realistic sample data records derived entirely from your real schema and lookup values.', provide: 'Nothing — add a number 1–3 for more records. Writes JSON to artefacts/sample-data/.' },
              { cmd: '/generate-ai-feature-registry', use: 'Scans the codebase and drafts a registry of every AI feature — trigger, code location, flag, status.', provide: 'Nothing — just run it. Writes artefacts/product-docs/ai-feature-review/ai-features.md.' },
              { cmd: '/ai-feature-data-audit', use: 'Traces exactly what data feeds one AI feature — tables, fields, filters — plus a QA testing guide.', provide: 'The AI feature name. Presented in the response; saved only if you ask.' },
              { cmd: '/generate-ai-feature-dependency-map', use: 'Maps which product modules each AI feature depends on, and the impact if one is disabled.', provide: 'Nothing — just run it (or name a feature).' },
            ].map((row) => (
              <tr class="bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top whitespace-nowrap">
                  <span class="font-mono text-xs text-violet-700 dark:text-violet-400">{row.cmd}</span>
                  {row.beta && (
                    <span class="ml-2 rounded-full border border-amber-300 bg-amber-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-amber-700 dark:border-amber-700/50 dark:bg-amber-900/30 dark:text-amber-400">Beta</span>
                  )}
                </td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">{row.use}{row.beta && <span class="text-zinc-400 dark:text-zinc-500"> (experimental)</span>}</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 align-top text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">{row.provide}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Tips for beginners -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white">Tips for getting the best results</h2>
      <div class="mt-6 space-y-4">
        {[
          {
            title: 'You never need to structure your input',
            body: 'Paste raw emails, Slack messages, voice transcripts, or Google Doc excerpts exactly as they are. Baxter extracts what it needs. The messier the input, the more value Baxter adds.',
          },
          {
            title: 'Coderepo is the key to verification',
            body: 'Baxter automatically reads coderepo/ before writing every non-BRD artefact — without being asked, every time. Without it, artefact verification cannot run and Baxter will explicitly flag every field, module, and route it could not confirm. For production teams, always add your codebase.',
          },
          {
